==English==
{{wikipedia|dab=Perennial (disambiguation)|Perennial}}

===Etymology===
1644, from {{bor|en|la|perennis||lasting through the whole year}}, from {{m|la|per-||through}} + {{m|la|annus||year}} + [[-al]]; [[Wiktionary:Etymology#Surface_etymologies|surface analysis]] {{confix|en|per|ennial}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/pəˈɹɛni.əl/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-perennial.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Lasting or remaining active throughout the {{l|en|year}}, or all the time.
#: {{ux|en|a '''perennial''' stream}}
# {{lb|en|botany|of a plant}} Having a life cycle of more than two years. Compare {{m|en|annual}}, {{m|en|biennial}}.
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} Continuing without {{l|en|cessation}} or {{l|en|intermission}}; {{l|en|perpetual}}; {{l|en|permanent}}; {{l|en|unceasing}}; never {{l|en|failing}}.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1790|authorlink=Edmund Burke|first=Edmund|last=Burke|title=[[s:Reflections on the Revolution in France|Reflections on the Revolution in France]]|passage=The '''perennial''' existence of bodies corporate and their fortunes are things particularly suited to a man who has long views…}}
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} {{l|en|enduring|Enduring}}; {{l|en|lasting}}; {{l|en|timeless}}.
#: {{ux|en|His artwork has a '''perennial''' beauty.}}
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} {{l|en|recurrent|Recurrent}}; appearing or recurring again and again.
#: {{ux|en|Change is a '''perennial''' theme in politics.}}

